  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — 4 soft slashes routed via agent; spec FR-50 + Phase D exit criterion 3 binding".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 082 status is 🔲, dep 080 is ✅. Update `current-task.md` to 082.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read CommandRouter.ts (task 080). Read chat-architecture.md + AI-ARCHITECTURE.md to identify the BFF chat-endpoint payload schema. Verify CapabilityRouter Layer 1 consumes a `commandIntent` field (extend Layer 1 if needed — minimal change; verify no new public-contract surface is added).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author SoftSlashRouter">
      Create `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/SoftSlashRouter.ts`. Implement `decorateMessage(intent, message)` that sets `commandIntent`. Map each soft slash to its intent value. Telemetry per ADR-015.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify CapabilityRouter Recognizes commandIntent">
      Confirm in BFF chat-endpoint code (`Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs`) that Layer 1 already reads or can be minimally extended to consume `commandIntent`. If extension needed: add a single deterministic lookup in Layer 1 that pre-selects route. NO new public-contract surface; NO new DI registration.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire into ConversationPane">
      In `ConversationPane.tsx`, when `intent.isSoftSlash === true`, call `SoftSlashRouter.decorateMessage(intent, message)` then send via existing path. Hard slashes (081) are intercepted before this branch; natural language flows through unchanged.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Composition with References">
      Test composition: `/summarize #engagement-letter.docx` — intent has command + references[]. Verify BFF payload includes both. (Reference resolution itself is task 083.)
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + Test + Verify Conversational Primacy">
      Run build + test. Confirm `/draft summarize that for me` still gets a conversational response (NFR-01). Confirm typing without slash still routes via existing path (NFR-11).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify ADR-013 (no new facade), ADR-015 (telemetry hygiene), NFR-01 + NFR-11. If CapabilityRouter extension touched BFF code: verify publish-size delta is &lt;100 KB and recorded. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status. Update TASK-INDEX.md: 082 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report completion + downstream unblock (084).
    </step>
  </steps>

